  "text": "Drosophila has ®ve Rad51 family members DmRad51/spnA is predicted to encode a 336 amino acid protein. It shows 55.1% identity to S.cerevisiae Rad51 over the entire protein ( Figure 3A ; [CITATION_1] . Even higher conservation is observed in sequence align- A multiple sequence alignment, using complete protein sequences from known S.cerevisiae, human and Drosophila Rad51 family members, was assembled by the CLUSTAL V method [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , which is included in the MegAlign module of the Lasergene sequence analysis software suite (DNASTAR, Inc.), and utilizing PAM250 residue weighting. E.Staeva-Vieira, S.Yoo and R.Lehmann ment with the mouse and human Rad51 (64.6% identical and~80% similar) ( Figure 3A ; [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . There were four members of the Drosophila Rad51 family identi®ed from the Genome Project, rad51-like (CG7948; spnA), spnB (CG3325), rad51C (CG2412) and rad51D (CG6318) [CITATION_6] and a Rad51C-like protein (CG31069), which was shown to be encoded by spindle-D ( Figure 3A± C; [CITATION_7] . Alignment comparison of all ®ve Drosophila Rad51 family members reveals that SpnA protein is the most similar to yeast and human Rad51 ( Figure 3A and C). This similarity is not only restricted to the RecA core domain (72.2% identical to HsRAD51) but extends to the N-terminus (49.6%) and C-terminus (74.1%) ( Figure 3B ). Phylogenetic analysis shows that the other Drosophila members, SpnB, SpnD, Rad51C and Rad51D, are more similar to the Rad51 accessory proteins HsXRCC3, HsRAD51C, HsRAD51D and ScRad55 (or HsXRCC2), respectively ( Figure 3C ; [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . Based on genome annotation and sequence similarity, we conclude that Spindle-A is the structural homolog of the yeast and mammalian Rad51 protein.",
